<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer14722930319096270734">Linda Sue Park is a Korean American author of children&apos;s fiction. Park published her first novel, Seesaw Girl, in 1999. To date, she has written six children’s novels and five picture books for younger readers. Park’s work achieved prominence when she received the prestigious 2002 Newbery Medal for her novel A Single Shard.<br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText14722930319096270734" style="display:none">Linda Sue Park is a Korean American author of children's fiction. Park published her first novel, Seesaw Girl, in 1999. To date, she has written six children’s novels and five picture books for younger readers. Park’s work achieved prominence when she received the prestigious 2002 Newbery Medal for her novel A Single Shard.<br /><br /></span>
